<sect1 id="DaysBetween">
  <!-- DNT-Start --><title>DaysBetween</title><!-- DNT-End -->

  <!-- DNT-Start --><para><emphasis role="bold">STD.Date.DaysBetween<indexterm>
      <primary>STD.Date.DaysBetween</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>DaysBetween</primary>
    </indexterm>(</emphasis> <emphasis role="bold">fromDate,
  toDate)</emphasis></para><!-- DNT-End -->

  <informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
    <tgroup cols="2">
      <colspec colwidth="80.50pt" />

      <colspec />

      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry><!-- DNT-Start --><emphasis>fromDate</emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

          <entry>The first date value in Date_t format.</entry>
        </row>

        <row>
          <entry><!-- DNT-Start --><emphasis>toDate</emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

          <entry>The last date value in Date_t format.</entry>
        </row>

        <row>
          <entry><!-- DNT-Start -->Return:<!-- DNT-End --></entry>

          <entry><!-- DNT-Start -->DaysBetween<!-- DNT-End --> returns an <!-- DNT-Start -->INTEGER<!-- DNT-End --> value of the number of days
          between the two dates.</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>

  <para>The <emphasis role="bold"><!-- DNT-Start -->DaysBetween<!-- DNT-End --></emphasis> function calculates
  the number of whole days between two dates.</para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <!-- DNT-Start --><programlisting format="linespecific">IMPORT STD;
StartDate := 19631122;
numDays := STD.Date.DaysBetween(startDate,STD.Date.Today());
      // numDays contains the number of days between the startDate and today's date
</programlisting><!-- DNT-End -->

  <para></para>
</sect1>
